%N A131488 a(n) is the number of polyhexes with n edges, including inner edges.
%C A131488 An n-celled polyhex with perimeter p has (6n+p)/2 edges. The maximum number of edges in an n-celled polyhex is 5n+1.
%C A131488 Given Clarke's table T(p,n), a(n) is an antidiagonal sum selecting entries in a (1,3)-leaper's moves. - _R. J. Mathar_, Feb 23 2021
%H A131488 Andrew Clarke, <a href="http://www.recmath.com/PolyPages/PolyPages/IsopolyH.htm">Isoperimetrical Polyhexes</a>
%e A131488 a(31) = T(p=26,A=6) + T(p=20,A=7) = 36+3 = 39. a(34) = T(p=26,A=7) + T(p=20,A=8) = 69+1 = 70. a(35) = 107+9. a(36) = 118+21. a(41) = 411+155+1. a(44) = 1621 +123. a(45) = 1986+420+2. a(46) = 1489+1046+26. - _R. J. Mathar_, Feb 23 2021
